# Netlify-style routing rules. Lovable publish + Netlify + Cloudflare Pages
# all honor this file. Order matters: more specific rules first.
#
# CRITICAL: We MUST try the prerendered per-route file before falling back to
# the SPA index.html. Without this, every route gets the homepage HTML and
# the entire site canonicals to "/" for crawlers (catastrophic SEO).
#
# Netlify automatically serves static files in dist/ before applying rewrites,
# so dist/ai-checker/index.html is served for /ai-checker. The catch-all below
# is ONLY for client-side routes the prerender list missed (deep blog post
# URLs not yet in prerender-routes.ts, dynamic /help-article/* slugs, etc.).

# Force https + apex domain (one canonical host)
https://aifreetextpro.lovable.app/*  https://aifreetextpro.com/:splat  301!
https://www.aifreetextpro.com/*      https://aifreetextpro.com/:splat  301!

# SPA fallback — runs LAST, only when no static file matched
/*  /index.html  200
